name: microservice-wallet-system
description: This is the backend system for the E-Wallet application, built with a microservices architecture to ensure scalability and maintainability. The system is composed of several microservices, including the Auth microservice for authentication and token management, the Wallet microservice for managing wallet operations and in-app transactions etc.

name: Credit-Management-System-With-Spring-Cloud
description: Microservices in Spring Boot including microservices for managing client data, credit evaluation, and card issuance. Secure access with JWT tokens and Keycloak. Utilizes both synchronous and asynchronous communication patterns with OpenFeign and RabbitMQ. Docker is used for containerization.

name: microservices-system-3nodejs-1LB
description: Step by Step Basic Microservices System (3 NodeJS + 1 Load Balancer containers) with Docker Compose

name: Product-Management-System-Java-Spring-Boot-Microservices
description: Microsservice architeccture used to create this project. there are three microservices and communicate each other using asyncronous communication.

name: Car-Bidding-System
description: This Repository will provide the backend functionality of the Car Bidding System using Microservices Architecture.

name: numer
description: A microservices backend to support an invoice management system.

name: E-Commerce-Microservices-Architecture
description: The project is built with Docker for containerization, Spring Boot for creating microservices, Kafka for messaging and event streaming, and Spring Cloud for managing the distributed system.

name: node-notification-microservice
description: A scalable, multi-channel notification microservice designed to efficiently handle and dispatch notifications via Email, SMS, and Push channels. Ideal for integrating into distributed systems with robust support for fault tolerance and high-throughput environments.

name: Microservices_3.0
description: A Spring Boot 3.0 project demonstrating the creation of microservices architecture. It includes service discovery, API gateway, load balancing, and communication between services using REST and messaging systems. The project highlights scalability, fault tolerance, and independent deployment of services for modern cloud-native applications.

name: ERP-System
description: Development of an ERP system using microservices architecture to integrate customer services, products, inventory, shipping and payments. Implementation of REST APIs for communication between modules, ensuring data verification and order processing. Use of RabbitMQ for messaging and event exchange between services,

name: event-management-system
description: An Event Management System built with microservices architecture using Spring Boot. It allows users to browse, book, and manage event tickets. Features include user management, event handling, ticket booking, payment processing, notifications, and analytics, demonstrating RESTful API design and industry standards.

name: grapevine-p2p-chat
description: Grapevine P2P Chat is a decentralized, peer-to-peer chat app built with the Bitfinex Grenache microservice framework, using the BitTorrent DHT protocol for service discovery. It enables real-time, serverless communication between peers, offering a fault-tolerant, fully decentralized messaging system.

name: Charging-Station
description: Developed a charging-station platform with four microservices: Charging-session (using PostgreSQL), Charger (using MongoDB), User, and Port. Integrated Kafka for communication between Port and Charging-session, with a scheduler to manage updates. The system displays nearby charging locations and indicates port availability for charging
